Today Rocket, the Big Beefy Boy, is wearing his Angry Eyes.
.

Here is Rocket, looking to the heavens in desperate hope that we as a nation are not completely brought to our knees by a Tory government. Rocket, the big beefy boy, cares deeply about this green and pleasant land.
.
His brothers on the other hand give little care for the state of affairs. Milky is currently travelling the Greek islands with his feline friend Dolores and Orbit, as ever, is chasing that cash dollar.
.
His close mates from ‚Äòdown the alley‚Äô assure him that with his ever rising insta fame, he‚Äôll soon be attracting a myriad of sweet, sweet brand deals. Failing that, next year he plans to apply for Love Island. That‚Äôll sort it.
.
All the kitties send you love (except Orbit, he just wants your money), and ask that you give this post some love. Rocket would like to remind you that he‚Äôs the best and is his Mummy‚Äôs ‚Äòbig beefy boy‚Äô. üêæ

Here is Venus soaking up the sun and shutting his eyes. Venus hopes that when he opens them, women‚Äôs reproductive rights won‚Äôt be controlled by old white men who would probably love to have a bit of ‚Äòreproductive activity‚Äô with a woman.
.
Venus can‚Äôt really believe the world is going backwards. Venus feels for his human friends in Northern Ireland, America and other countries in the world who are robbed of the opportunity to make their own choices.
.
Even Rocket, the big beefy boy, has taken a moment away from contemplating the perils of Brexit, to reflect on this disgusting news.
.
It is a sad day for our kitty friends around the world.
.
The cats wish they could be more witty and light hearted today but they are too busy stitching their hand maid uniforms to crack jokes.
.
üêæ

Cosmo and Venus have been settling in nicely.
.
They have learnt where to ‚Äòdo poopsies‚Äô, have found the best spots to snooze and much to Rocket‚Äôs Branxiety, have joined the Green Party.
.
Cosmo and Venus think we should shove Brexit up our human bottoms and focus on the climate crisis we are all urgently facing.
.
Cosmo and Venus can‚Äôt use plastic bags or buy fast fashion because their brains are small and they have no hands, but if they could, they wouldn‚Äôt.
.
The babies ask that you make a climate positive choice today and also that you share this absolutely ridiculous account with a friend. Orbit wants to start doing ads and impress his mate Dave. You know how it is. üëåüèª

Cosmo and Venus are yet to decide how they feel about the political landscape as they were not born when it all went to their dogs.
.
Cosmo and Venus would quite like another vote, sans false information, so they can have a chance to stay pally with their continental kitty friends.
.
Until then, they ask that you give this account some love, tag a fellow #catlady and leave a üêæ!

Today Rocket is spending some much needed time alone. Rocket feels very torn. He is both deeply concerned AND sick to death of hearing about Brexit. He‚Äôs tried not thinking about it, he‚Äôs stockpiled his meaty pouches, he‚Äôs considered leaving the country but he has found no solace and so today, is Under The Chair.
. 
Milky and Orbit have tried to persuade him out for a spot of catnip with them and Dolores, but he has refused. ‚ÄòWhy bother enjoying anything when the government is on such shaky ground?‚Äô, Rocket wonders.
.
The other four cats would like to echo that they don‚Äôt subscribe to Rocket‚Äôs pessimism and would love it if you gave his picture some love to cheer him up. Poor old Rocket. üêæ‚ù§Ô∏èüêæ

The glamorous life I lead! Took the fur babies (and the human baby) to the vet because one had a little lump that has now gone, but we suspect was a tick.
.
They‚Äôve both had a protective spray, worming meds and are booked in for vaccines next month so should all be golden! Phew!!
.
Now I‚Äôm home and cooking a 5 star meal full of nutrients and flavour that both my children will eat all of with glad hearts. Ahaha hilarious. üêæüí´üíñ

This is a box of kittens. They are Milky and Orbit‚Äôs biological siblings and 2 now live with us, 2 live next door and 1 very near by!
.
Milky and Orbit have welcomed them with nothing but the finest disdain and Rocket gives about as many shizzles as Dolores does for Milky‚Äôs lost bits. Ie. None.
.
For those on tender hooks, Dolores has forgiven Milky for his feminist faux pas. She understands he is learning to be an ally and it‚Äôs progress, not perfection.
.
The kittens do have names and they‚Äôll be revealed shortly. Any space themed guesses so far? üêæ‚ù§Ô∏è

Today is #internationalwomensday but Milky has effed up and had a foolish row with Dolores.
.
Dolores is a feminist feline and thought her new boyfriend was too.
.
This morning though, over a meaty pouch in jelly, Milky asked Dolores when it was International Men‚Äôs Day.
.
Trying not to choke on her tuna chunk, Dolores told him it‚Äôs officially November 19th but unofficially every single bl**dy day!
.
Milky was instantly sorry, he was only joking, but before he could atone for his mistake, Dolores had shown him the cat flap.
.
Milky has learnt a valuable lesson today. He asks that you support this post with a double tap and sympathetic comment if you can ever forgive him. He also asks if you can put in a good word with Dolores because he‚Äôs already put the deposit down on those Lanzarote flights. üêæ

Yesterday was a big day for the lads. Rocket, Milky and Orbit returned to catstagram and the world was shookith.
.
Rocket and Milky want to remind you that fame won‚Äôt change them. Rocket is rooted to the callings of his noble Scottish ancestors and Milky cares only for his new (and very accepting) beau, Dolores and their upcoming trip to Lanzarote. They intend to feel the volcanic ash under their paws and the hot sun on their furs.
.
Orbit however, has ‚Äògone off the rails‚Äô. He plans to undertake a full UK meet & greet tour and is currently drawing up designs for his merch- apparently Clive knows a man who knows someone with a hoodie contact. Orbit hopes he will have his low quality, highly priced hoodies on sale soon.
.
Fame and fortune are tricky beasts to manage but all three appreciate you sticking by them on this journey and ask that you like this photo and leave any tips for dealing with the paps below. Rocket would also like to remind you that he is, in fact, a Big Beefy Boy. üêæ

It‚Äôs been a long time since Rocket, Orbit or Milky last posted. The state of our political affairs teamed with the increasing pressure of fame they felt with this popular Instagram account led them to take stock.
.
Rocket spent most of winter travelling the Scottish Highlands and breathing that fresh air in. Here he is having a rest post trek.
.
Orbit remained true to his semi feral ways and roamed the town with a slightly unkempt alley cat named Clive. He came back with a greater understanding of his privilege and is now working with several feline charities to support kittens without homes.
.
Milky has felt the most joy on his sab-catical. He left home to find love. Sadly on this quest he discovered he has had the snip and so the act of physical kitty love was beyond him. Fortunately, his new found beau, Dolores, cares not for the hankypanky and is in love with Milky‚Äôs true self, his soul. They are planning a trip to Lanzarote this Spring.
.
And so the pets are rested and ready to return to their life of fame and insta fortune.
.
They ask you to like this image and leave a comment telling them who had the best break. Rocket reminds you he is a ‚Äòbig beefy boy‚Äô and would most like your votes. üêæ
It is Thursday and Milky is feeling despondent with the political landscape but hopeful that the John Lewis 2018 Christmas Ad will be out soon. Milky is a very complex boy.

It is Monday and Milky just wants Brexit to be ok, for us all to get along like we used to in middle school, he wishes he could bake a cake made out of rainbows and smiles and we‚Äôd all eat it and be happy. üåà
It is Tuesday and Orbit is ready to fight the patriarchy.
Today Orbit and Milky are cosplaying as Kanye and Trump.
It is Friday and Orbit is on his last nerve worrying about the latest plunge in The Dow Jones. Orbits stocks and shares will be in tatters now.
It is Thursday and as Orbit stares into the face of grabby doom, he wonders, 'what even IS brexit at this point?'
It is Wednesday and Orbit wonders if Donald Trump has watched The Handmaid's Tale.
It is Tuesday and so Orbit is thinking about all the people who voted 'Leave'.
It is Monday and Milky is thinking about Theresa May.
After staring each other out for 45 solid minutes, Orbit felt victorious. 'Take that you hoover nozzle, whose the winner now??', Orbit silently gloated.
Rocket is a minimalist. He wants a warm thigh, a bit of sofa and nothing else. Rocket is also considering going vegan but isn't quite there yet.
